# Phase 2: Capture Engine Implementation

## Goal
Implement a robust network capture engine by modularizing the existing background script logic and adding enhanced filtering and detection capabilities.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> This refactor moves core capture logic from [src/background/index.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/index.ts) to `src/background/capture/NetworkCapture.ts`.

## Proposed Changes

### [Shared Constants]

#### [NEW] [mimeTypes.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/shared/constants/mimeTypes.ts)
- Define `MEDIA_EXTENSIONS` and `MEDIA_MIME_PREFIXES`.
- Centralize all MIME type definitions.

### [Background Script]

#### [NEW] [NetworkCapture.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/capture/NetworkCapture.ts)
- Class `NetworkCapture` managing `webRequest` listeners.
- Implements:
  - [start()](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/index.ts#39-51) / [stop()](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/index.ts#52-59) methods.
  - [isMediaResource()](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/index.ts#183-214) detection (ported and enhanced).
  - Header capturing (`onSendHeaders`).
  - Response processing (`onResponseStarted`).
  - `CaptureRule` logic (using [Settings](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/shared/types/settings.ts#5-24): regex, blacklist/whitelist, size, MIME).

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/index.ts)
- Remove inline listener logic.
- Initialize and use `NetworkCapture` instance.
- Pass store actions to `NetworkCapture`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Build verification (`npm run build`).

### Manual Verification
- Load extension.
- Visit a media site (e.g., test page with video).
- Verify media is captured and appears in the popup/store.
- Test filtering (disable capture in settings, verify no capture).
